Dialogue: 1,0:16:06.36,0:16:08.11,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,0)\shad0\bord1.2\fs11\fscx85\c&H141416&\4c&H171718&\3c&HC2C6BB&\fax0.1\frx14\fry8\pos(325,270)\frz17.34}Nationality
Dialogue: 1,0:16:06.36,0:16:08.11,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,0)\shad0\bord1.2\fs12\c&H141416&\4c&H171718&\3c&HC2C6BB&\fax0.1\pos(435,236)\frz17.99\frx20\fry12}England
Dialogue: 1,0:16:06.36,0:16:08.11,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,0)\shad0\bord1.2\fs12\c&H141416&\4c&H171718&\3c&HC2C6BB&\frz16.5\fax0.1\frx14\fry8\pos(334,286)}Car
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.11,0:16:12.02,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,It's like he's moving on a combination \Nof reflexes and split-second improvisation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.57,0:16:17.53,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,I've been racing for a long time, \Nbut I've never seen anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.30,0:16:31.30,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru to booth. Tell me where the 86 is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:37.01,Default,Yamatani,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that. Just focus on your\N surroundings. You're in the death zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.50,0:16:41.19,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, when you reply like that, \Nit just makes me even {\i1}more{\i0} curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.77,0:16:47.98,Italics,Yamatani,0000,0000,0000,,If you really wanna know, the 86 has passed \Nthe 10, and he's now 15 seconds ahead of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.81,0:16:50.80,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,He's that far ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.71,0:16:53.82,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Is he insane?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:57.62,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,How can he drive like that in this fog?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.14,0:17:05.54,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here. The 8 car, the Porsche, \Nis 3.6 seconds ahead. Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.87,0:17:07.77,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Roger. {\fnTrebuchet MS}I'll catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:14.38,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,This is nuts, Kanata. Totally nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.98,0:17:17.68,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You're in my 86 that goes\N for 1.7 million yen used...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:22.64,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,and you're closing in on a Carerra GTS \Nthat costs 20 million with options!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.34,0:17:26.33,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you realize Porsche \Nmakes world-class sports cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.65,0:17:28.60,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,The kind I'll never afford?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.39,0:17:33.65,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here. Two seconds flat. Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:34.44,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:42.37,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'm figuring out the point\N of this voice countdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.14,0:17:48.18,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's the data he needs to grasp where he is \Nand where the car in front is relative to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.51,0:17:55.63,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,He's able to simulate where \Nhe'll catch up to the car in front...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.82,0:18:00.13,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,And by the time the other car\N emerges from the fog,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.13,0:18:03.17,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,he already has a plan to overtake it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:09.73,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just technique that makes\N Kanata's driving superhuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.99,0:18:15.28,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's the way his brain is able \Nto interpret all of that info.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.21,0:18:25.45,Italics,Second,0000,0000,0000,,Watch yourself, Jackson! There's a car \Ncoming up on you at amazing speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.67,0:18:29.72,Default,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Pardon? {\fnTrebuchet MS}What'd you say? I don't follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.72,0:18:34.17,Italics,Second,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to tell you \Nthe 86 is gaining on you, fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.13,0:18:40.09,Italics,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,What's he going on about? \NThis is no time for jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:42.37,Italics,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the middle of the death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.68,0:18:48.02,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here. One second exactly. Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.47,0:18:49.52,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:18:51.10,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:52.06,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Four.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.06,0:18:53.23,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:54.11,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:54.86,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}One.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:58.65,Default,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:06.45,Italics,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,He's going full throttle \Nin the middle of all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:07.95,Italics,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,Is he suicidal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:13.13,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 is going through on the 8!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:18.97,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But Taylor's not backing down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.97,0:19:22.39,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,They're side-by-side, \Nwith the fog wrecking their visibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:26.72,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It's a terrifying sight! \NEnough to give you chills just watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:28.81,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Neither man is driving sensibly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.78,0:19:34.30,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,This is the kind of fearless driving \Nthat gives MFG racers their reputation!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:40.11,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Neither is giving way! \NWho will come out on top?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:54.87,Italics,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna keep this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.29,0:19:58.38,Italics,Taylor,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like risking my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.90,0:20:04.30,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Taylor gradually fades.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.30,0:20:07.06,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And the 86 pulls ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:11.06,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's made it up into ninth place! \NHe's in single digits!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.24,0:20:13.38,Default,Customer,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.38,0:20:15.66,Default,Customer,0000,0000,0000,,Katagiri Kanata is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.83,0:20:20.01,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Kogashiwa-san, don't just sit there.\N What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.01,0:20:23.85,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I don't even know \Nwhat to say at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.62,0:20:28.20,Default,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Just watching that was scary enough for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.85,0:20:33.51,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the poor visibility, he drove\Nthose three corners with surgical precision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.35,0:20:37.71,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Taylor-kun tried to demonstrate the \Npride that put him to eighth last year,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:39.46,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,but it only took him so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.53,0:20:45.83,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Something about Katagiri-kun \Nis fundamentally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:50.88,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,This is just speculation on my part,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.88,0:20:55.14,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,but I think Katagiri Kanata\N might have a clear idea
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.14,0:20:58.06,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,of what this course \Nlooks like without the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.27,0:21:00.53,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But this is his first time competing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:04.11,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,This should be the first time \Nhe's raced on an MFG road course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.11,0:21:06.16,Default,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,You're right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.65,0:21:12.54,Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,But I have to wonder if he has some kind \Nof unique memorization ability others don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.19,0:21:19.81,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,And that might be the special element
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.81,0:21:25.25,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,that makes Katagiri Kanata's \Nextraordinary performance possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.83,0:21:29.43,Default,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, Kogashiwa. That's going overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.86,0:21:33.85,Default,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,I know he's Fujiwara's student, \Nbut you don't have to hype him up that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.04,0:21:40.82,Default,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,That said, in qualifying, it seemed like \Nhe was copying the demo run perfectly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.82,0:21:45.78,Default,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,whereas in the race, he's been \Nchanging it up to better suit his own style.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.72,0:21:48.66,Default,Keisuke,0000,0000,0000,,He's a smart kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.34,0:23:35.70,Italics,Narration,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Turn 09: The 300 kph Dogfight.